# Cursor Rules — FixMyPrompt

## Project
Chrome Extension (Manifest V3, vanilla JS). No frameworks. Bundled with esbuild.
Works on chatgpt.com and claude.ai.

## Stack
- Vanilla JS (ES modules in src/, IIFE output after build)
- esbuild for bundling
- Node.js + Express backend on Railway
- OpenAI GPT-4 Turbo for prompt rewriting

## Critical rules
- Never hardcode `platform: 'chatgpt'` — use `_detectPlatform()` from auto-detect-balloon.js
- Backend returns scores 0–100. UI shows 0–10. Always divide by 10 when displaying.
- `balloonShownInCurrentConversation` in button.js must only reset on a genuine new conversation (different URL UUID), not on every URL change.
- No npm packages unless absolutely necessary — check bundle size impact first.
- All console.log must use `[FixMyPrompt]` prefix.
- Do not add comments or docstrings to code that isn't being changed.

## Key files
- `src/content/button.js` — balloon trigger, conversation detection, ✨ button
- `src/content/auto-detect-balloon.js` — balloon UI (6 states)
- `src/shared/backend-api.js` — Railway API client + score normalization
- `src/shared/domain-detector.js` — classifies prompts into 8 domains

## Build output
Always goes to `FixMyPrompt/` directory. After any src/ change, rebuild before testing.
